   <titleInfo>
      <title>Letter, John Watkins in Knoxville, Tenn. to Sarah Probert in Pittsfield, Ohio, 1864 January 3</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>In this letter, dated January 3, 1864, from John Watkins in Knoxville, Tenn., to Sarah Probert in Pittsfield, Ohio, Watkins complains that changes in the mail route have resulted in a decrease in letters from home. He writes also of General Foster's order to stabilize prices and the anger it has caused among Knoxville merchants. He points out that local farmers have also come into town, complaining that the Confederate occupation of the area has left them nearly "destitute."</abstract>
